Server Creation - Nodjs + Express

Basic Commands
--------------
1) Creating package.json - npm init
2) Creating node modules - npm i express (Install Express)
3) Install nodemon - npm install -g nodemon
4) Run - nodmon index.js
5) npm i mongoose

Basic Steps
----------

) Creating a folder (BankServer)
2) Create package.json file
3) Install Express
4) Creating index page
5) import exprss inside index.js file
6) Create an app using ecxpress
7) Setup the port number
8) Resolving http request

9) HTTP Response code
    1xx - information
    2xx - Successful
    3xx - Redirection
    4xx - Client Error
    5xx - Server Error

10) JWT Token
    To install token - npm i jsonwebtoken
    To generate token - sign()

11) Middleware
    it comes in the middle of the request and the response cycle of the nodejs execution

    req,res,next

    1. Application Specific Midleware - for entire application
    2. Router Specific Midleware - for token verification -verify()

12) Database integration

    1. Install mongoose - npm i mongoose 

13) Asynchronous function resolving - promise

    1. Resolving state - .then()
    2. reject state - .catch()

14) CORS - Cross Origin Resource Sharing

    install cros - npm i cors

    port 4200(Angular) -----(request)------port 3000(node) (req-received)

15) Asynchronous call -RxJs -(Reactive Extension for javascript)

    js - promise
    ts - RxJs(library)

        1. Observable
            a) resolved - Subscribe()
            b) reject - catch()